Benefits:
• A bot will post in the announcements channel whenever the {Broadcaster} goes live. 
• {Broadcaster}s can enter TV-voice channels directly, and move anyone from 
the assembly-hall voice channel to join them in TV-voice. This feature is used to protect broadcasts from intrusion by random server users. 
• {Broadcasters}s can create “Events” in the Alchemy server to mark their presentations on the calendar. 
• {Broadcaster}s are often invited by Alchemy leadership to broadcast guild-organized events and/or events with guild-created resources (for example, a tournament played on maps created by Alchemy members).

Requirements:
• Be an Alchemy Affiliate.
• Include the !discord command in the chat of their broadcast, providing viewers a link to the Alchemy server. That link must constitute no less than 50% of the total number of links shared in this way.
• Refrain from introducing anyone to either TV-voice channel without certainty that they belong there.

Additional Notes:
- This is a passive role, awarded because someone is already doing something for their own objectives, unmotivated by direction from the rest of the community. As such, there are no "responsibilities", although if we fill up our stream notification bot limit, we may have to ask inactive streamers to step aside and make room for other more active persons.
